  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "38. But Paul thought not good to take him with them who departed from them—that is, who had departed; but the word is stronger than this—\"who stood aloof\" or \"turned away\" from them.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "from Pamphylia, and went not with them to the work—the work yet before them. The allusion is to what is recorded in Ac 13:13 (see on [2027]Ac 13:13).",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
